## üéØ **OPTION 1: Use Your Local Backend (Easiest)**

If you want to test quickly, you can use your local backend with ngrok:

### **A. Install ngrok** (One-time setup)
```bash
# Install via Homebrew
brew install ngrok

# Or download from: https: //ngrok.com/download
```

### **B. Start Your Backend** (Already running!)
Your backend is already running on port 3001 ‚úÖ

### **C. Expose Backend with ngrok**
```bash
# In a new terminal
ngrok http 3001
```

This will give you a public URL like:
```
https: //abc123.ngrok.io
```

### **D. Set Environment Variable in Vercel**
1. Go to [vercel.com/dashboard
](https: //vercel.com/dashboard)
2. Select your project
3. Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
4. Add:
   ```
   Name: VITE_API_URL
   Value: https: //abc123.ngrok.io/api
   ```
5. Redeploy frontend

**Pros**: Quick, no backend deployment needed  
**Cons**: ngrok URL changes when you restart (free tier)

